decks.notes: This deck focuses on utilizing the synergy between Slimefoot and Squee to create a constant stream of aggro threats while also having recursion and sacrifice outlets to keep the pressure on the opponent. The deck aims to quickly build up a board presence with efficient creatures like Elves and Goblins, while also being able to disrupt the opponent's strategy with removal and disruption spells. By combining the token generation of Slimefoot with the recurring abilities of Squee, the deck can overwhelm the opponent with an army of saprolings while also maintaining a steady flow of threats to keep the pressure on. The deck's versatility and ability to adapt to different situations make it a formidable force in one-on-one matchups.

The main strategy of this deck is to control the game by interacting with the opponent's spells and board state while drawing cards and generating value through Kess, Dissident Mage's ability to cast spells from the graveyard. The deck includes a wide variety of control elements such as counterspells, removal spells, and card draw. It also features powerful cards like Cruel Ultimatum and Sheoldred, the Apocalypse to help close out the game once the opponent has been neutralized. By efficiently managing resources and disrupting the opponent's game plan, the deck aims to establish dominance and secure a victory through attrition and incremental advantage.
